# ─── Boule environment ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy to .env and fill in. NEVER commit .env. Boule also reads these straight
# from the process environment, which is the recommended path for CI.

# Claude — powers the Claude Agent SDK fleet. Provide ONE of:
#   1. CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN — a Claude Code token from `claude setup-token`
#      (uses your Claude Pro/Max subscription; preferred, especially for CI), or
#   2. ANTHROPIC_API_KEY — a metered Anthropic API key, or
#   3. nothing here + an existing `claude login` session (SDK auto-discovers it locally).
CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# GitHub — the system of record. Provide ONE of the following:
#   1. A fine-grained PAT, or
#   2. GitHub App installation credentials (preferred for autonomous CI bots).
# Required permissions: Issues: read/write, Projects: read/write,
# Discussions: read/write, Contents: read, Metadata: read.
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# GitHub App (alternative to GITHUB_TOKEN; preferred for autonomous CI bots).
# Named BOULE_APP_* on purpose: GitHub Actions forbids secret names starting with `GITHUB_`,
# so as Actions secrets these must be BOULE_APP_ID / BOULE_APP_INSTALLATION_ID / BOULE_APP_PRIVATE_KEY.
# BOULE_APP_ID=
# BOULE_APP_INSTALLATION_ID=
# Private key accepts a raw PEM, a file path, or — best for CI secret stores — a single-line
# base64 blob:  base64 -w0 your-app.private-key.pem   (macOS: base64 -i your-app.private-key.pem)
# BOULE_APP_PRIVATE_KEY=

# Target repository & project (can also live in .boule/config.yaml or be passed via --repo/--project)
# BOULE_REPO=owner/repo
# BOULE_PROJECT=1

# Optional: cap spend per run (USD). Boule aborts the run if exceeded.
# BOULE_BUDGET_USD=5
